A man died after a shooting incident on the corners of Church and Flatter roads in the Pietermaritzburg CBD on Wednesday morning. Paramedics reportedly found the body of a man believed to be in his 30’s lying on the sidewalk. “After paramedics assessed the man, it was found that he had sustained several gunshot wounds, leaving him in a critical condition. CPR and further advanced life support interventions were initiated in an effort to revive the patient. Sadly, the man was declared dead,” ER24 said. The cause of the incident is unknown and will form part of a South African Police Service investigation. -TNA Reporter